# Claude Skills

This directory contains symlinks to `../../agents/skills/*` for Claude Code auto-detection.

## How It Works

Claude Code automatically discovers skills in `.claude/skills/`. These are symlinks to the actual skill implementations in `agents/skills/`.

**Benefit**: Single source of truth - skills are maintained in one location but discoverable by Claude.

## Symlink Structure

```
.claude/skills/
├── README.md (this file)
└── <skill-name> → ../../agents/skills/<skill-name>
```

## Adding New Skills

When you create a new skill in `agents/skills/`, create a corresponding symlink:

### macOS/Linux

```bash
ln -s ../../agents/skills/<skill-name> .claude/skills/<skill-name>
```

### Windows

Requires Git symlink support:

```bash
git config core.symlinks true
```

Or use junction:

```cmd
mklink /J .claude\skills\<skill-name> ..\..\agents\skills\<skill-name>
```

